      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TEMPEST TIGER (7) turned in a moderate debut but last time hit the ground running and was never headed, leading throughout to land maiden success over 400m at this track (22.52). Has good ability and looks a key chance again. ICEBERG AHEAD (3) ran below best last time finishing sixth (25.79) over 450m at this track in a Grade 5. Has good speed and a low draw is a big help. Has ability and a bold showing is expected. SERGEANT DUKER (1) was safely held last time out, finishing seventh at Richmond Straight over 324m behind Despicable Leo (18.05) in a Grade 5. Was in the money prior to that. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Better than last start and can bounce back. MUSTANG ETHICS (6) didn't live up to the market support last time but cannot be taken lightly.",
